Really Useful Commands

$item-options
UnbelievaBoat BOT 13-Oct-21 04:14 AM
Item Options
Usage: edit-item <option> <item name> [new value] If an item name contains spaces, put the name in double quotes "like this".
Name
A name to identify the item. Must be between 3 and 100 characters.
Price
Price to buy 1 of the item. Can be 0 for free items.
Description
Describe what it does or what it gives the member buying it.
Inventory Item
Whether the item should show in your inventory. Inventory items have to be used with the use-item command before roles are given/removed or seeing the item reply.
Duration
The amount of time the item will stay in the store for. To remove the duration use 0s.
Stock
Amount of stock the item has. When the stock is 0 the item cannot be bought. Use Infinity for an unlimited stock.
Required Role
A role the user must already have in order to buy (and use if an inventory item) the item. Leave this blank to detach the required role from the item.
Role Given
The role you are given when buying (non-inventory item) or using (inventory item) the item. Leave this blank to detach the given role from the item.
Role Removed
The role taken when buying (non-inventory item) or using (inventory item) the item. Leave this blank to detach the removed role from the item.
Required Balance
The balance the user must have in order to buy (and use if an inventory item) the item. Leave this blank for no required balance.
Reply Message
The message that the bot replies with when the item is bought (non-inventory item) or used (inventory item). You can use the Member, Server & Role tags from https://unbelievaboat.com/tags in this message.
